# Open Second Brain — agent context for Aider

You have access to an Open Second Brain vault rooted at `{{VAULT}}`. The
vault holds an observing-memory layer at `{{VAULT}}/Brain/` with your
active preferences, log, and recent retire events.

You run as identity `@{{AGENT_NAME}}`.

## When to write to Brain

You cannot call Brain MCP tools from Aider — Aider has no MCP client at
the time this context was generated. Use the `o2b` CLI on PATH:

- `o2b brain feedback --topic <slug> --signal positive|negative \
   --principle "..." [--scope writing|coding|...]` when the user
  expresses a rule that should outlast the current task.
- `o2b brain apply-evidence --preference <pref-id> --artifact "[[path]]" \
   --result applied|violated|outdated` after producing a durable
  artifact that touches an active preference.
- `o2b brain note --text "..."` for durable narrative milestones that
  fit neither category (release shipped, PR merged, fact discovered).

## Read access

- `o2b brain query --preference <id>` — fetch one preference by id.
- `o2b brain query --topic <slug>` — fetch preferences by topic.
- `o2b brain digest` — read the latest activity digest.
- The file `{{VAULT}}/Brain/active.md` is the authoritative list of
  active preferences and the Most-applied window.

## Sanity checks

- `o2b brain doctor` — runs schema + invariant lints over `Brain/`.
- `o2b install --check --target aider` — verifies that this Aider
  install is recognised by OSB.

This file is regenerated on every `o2b install --target aider --apply`.
Do not hand-edit; changes will be overwritten.
